				\begin{document}$$ {\text{MRE }}\% = \left[ {\left( {C_{\text{i}} - \, C_{\text{f}} /C_{\text{i}} \, \times \, 100} \right)} \right] $$\end{document}MRE%=Ci-Cf/Ci×100where Ci represents the initial chromium metal ion concentration and Cf represents the final chromium metal ion concentration.
